      "message": "[Major] Line 445: 🟡 Suggestion: The one-second fallback clears an active search before slow daemon/network results can arrive, and `selectFirst_.exchange(false)` prevents `onSearchResultEnded` from selecting the eventual result. This makes global search unreliable under normal latency/offline-transition conditions. Prefer tying the timeout to an explicit failure/no-result path, or use a longer cancellable timer that only resets UI state after the search source confirms no pending search. For example:\n```suggestion\n// Start a cancellable fallback timer and stop it from onSearchResultEnded().\n// Do not exchange selectFirst_ here; leave result selection to the search completion path.\nsearchFallbackTimer_.start();\n```",
