      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 528: 🟡 Suggestion: `OriginalBody` only returns the current commit body. For edited messages, the edit UI now bypasses the displayed plugin-overwritten body, but it may still edit the latest raw body without considering the same action/body handling used by `Role::Body`. If the commit is an interaction action, this can populate the composer with an empty or incorrect string. Mirror the existing `Body` role fallback logic while intentionally skipping plugin display overrides. Example:\n```suggestion\ncase Role::OriginalBody: {\n    if (item.second.commit.contains(\"body\"))\n        return QVariant(item.second.commit.value(\"body\"));\n    return QVariant(item.second.body);\n}\n```",
